---
Source:
  - Title: Love Poems from God
    Page: 271
By: Theresa of Avila
Title: I Will Just Say This
---
We
bloomed in Spring.

Our bodies
are the leaves of God.

The apparent seasons of life and death
our eyes can suffer;


but our souls, dear, I will just say this forthrightï¼š
they are God
Himself,

we will never perish
unless He
does.
